        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 24 at 3:45PM MDT by NWS Salt Lake City UT</headline>
        <description>At 345 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Junction, moving northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Junction, Circleville, and Kingston.

This includes US Route 89 between mile markers 153 and 164.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
